=== Other honors ===
*United States Republican Senatorial Medal of Freedom<ref>{{citation|title=In Recognition of Mr. Albert Johnson|url=http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/CREC-2002-10-09/html/CREC-2002-10-09-pt1-PgS10221-4.htm|work=Congressional Record Volume 148, Number 132|publisher=Government Printing Office|accessdate=December 30, 2012|date=October 9, 2002}}</ref>
*Schwarzkopf Elementary School, named after him in [[Lutz, Florida]], 1991.<ref>{{citation|url=http://schwarzkopf.mysdhc.org/ |title=Schwarzkopf Elementary School |publisher=Schwarzkopf.mysdhc.org |date= |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>
*Honorary First-Class Private in the [[French Foreign Legion]], 1991.<ref>{{citation|agency=Reuters |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-07-25/news/mn-191_1_french-foreign-legion |title=General Schwarzkopf decorations |publisher=Articles.latimes.com | date=July 25, 1991 | accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>
*[[Distinguished German-American of the Year]], 2006.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.atlantic-times.com/archive_detail.php?recordID=741 |title=German-American honor |publisher=Atlantic-times.com |date= |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>
*Inducted in the [[New Jersey Hall of Fame]], 2008.<ref>{{citation|author=Tony Kurdzuk/The Star-Ledger | url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2008/05/new_jersey_hall_of_fame_welcom.html |title=New Jersey Hall of Fame |publisher=Nj.com |date= |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>
*[[Time Magazine]] cover on February 4, 1991, and April 1, 1996.<ref>{{citation|author= |url=http://www.time.com/time/covers/0,16641,19910204,00.html |title=Time-February 4, 1991 (cover) | work=Time |date=July 4, 1991 |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{citation| author= |url=http://www.time.com/time/covers/0,16641,19960401,00.html |title=Time-April 1, 1996 (cover)| work=Time | date=July 4, 1991 | accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref>
*Trail at [[Telluride Ski Resort]] renamed "Stormin' Normin", 2012.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2013/11/prweb11285751.htm |title=Telluride Ski Resort Honors US Army General Norman Schwarzkopf by Renaming Ski Run |publisher=PRWeb |date= November 1, 2013}}</ref>

